                    "company": "Brains On-Line BV",
                    "description": "Brains On-Line BV is a CRO for preclinical research in the field of developing new drugs aimed against brain-related diseases.\n\n2005-2011. Trial Manager for pharmacokinetic studies (DMPK), including development and validation of the MetaQuant microdialysis probe for quantitative analysis of compound concentrations in the brain, as well as introduction of the techniques for arterial and venous cannulations with automated blood sampling in a setting of freely moving.\n\n2011-present. Development and management of a quality control system for implementation into a GLP-like laboratory environment. This work includes the set-up of a computerized LIMS system for data management, and a quality handbook with descriptions of all work processes and procedural instructions.\n\nAt Brains On-Line I am the responsible officer for managing international transportation of animal by-products (e.g. samples of plasma, blood, CSF, tissue), that are frequently being shipped to/from the company. I maintain the nVWA licenses and supervise all required measures necessary to adhere to national and international regulations.\n\nWithin the Brains On-Line / Biomonitoring (RUG) work group I had teaching responsibilities to supervise PhD-students (5 in total), master projects of the RUG and Van Hall (9 in total), foreign fellows (2 in total), and numerous short-term C&O/FATEM undergraduate research projects.\n\nWithin the Brains On-Line / Biomonitoring (RUG) work group I was the coordinator of grant applications:\n** SenterNovem - innovation vouchers to stimulate small, innovative businesses\n** STW - grant application for pharmacokinetic research of BBB drug transport\n** NIH - grant application for microdialysis research on schizophrenia",
